Defendant in person.
On count 3, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by one (1) year extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant has credit for 4 days.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) maintain absolute sobriety;
2) maintain fulltime employment or employment at a level the agent determined is appropriate;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) submit to random drug screens and pay for same;
5) pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
On count 1, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years, consecutive to the prison sentence imposed on count 3, to commence upon defendant's discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation are the same as extended supervision conditions.
Minutes.
